div.h1: E820 Memory Map Parsing & Frame Allocator Initialization

div.p: Type 1 (USABLE): RAM, can be allocated Type 2 (RESERVED): BIOS, ROM, unavailable Type 3 (ACPI Reclaim): ACPI tables (reclaimable after init) Type 4 (ACPI NVS): ACPI non-volatile storage Type 5 (Unusable): Bad memory
BIOS EBDA: 0x9FC00-0x9FFFF ACPI tables: 0x20000000-0x203FFFFF BIOS ROM: 0xFFFC0000-0xFFFFFFFF
sizeof=32KB for 512MB Each bit = 1 frame (4KB) 0 = free, 1 = allocated
Step 1: Zero entire bitmap Step 2: Mark reserved regions Step 3: Mark kernel image Step 4: Mark bitmap itself Step 5: Count free frames
